<div id="maintext">
<dl>
<dt><div class="box"></div><b>My Research interests</b></dt>
<br>
<dd>Mostly combinatorial problems from high-energy physics and a bit of statistical physics, and from low-dimensional topology and geometry on the mathematical side.
<br>
<em>Combinatorial physics is one of the two axes of the <a href="https://lipn.univ-paris13.fr/en/calin"> CALIN</a> team in <a href="https://lipn.univ-paris13.fr/en/">LIPN</a>!</em>
<br>
<div style="width: 400px; display: inline-block;">
<ul>
<li>Combinatorial methods in quantum gravity</li>
<li>Combinatorics of graphs, trees, maps and higher dimensional structures</li>
<li>Random matrix models and random tensor models</li>
<li>Topological gauge theories, quantum invariants of manifolds</li>
<li>Spin networks and spin foam models</li>
<li>Combinatorics of low-dimensional topology and geometry</li>
</ul>
</div>
<div style="width: 300px; display:inline-block;">
</div>
<div style="width:320px; height:220px; display:inline-block;"> <img src="NonMelonicGraphColors.png" alt="" style="width:300px;height:220px;">
</div>
</dd>

<br>
<dt><div class="box"></div><b>Publications</b></dt>
<br>
<div style="width: 700px; display: inline-block; vertical-align: top;">
<dd>All preprints available <a href="http://arxiv.org/find/all/1/au:+bonzom/0/1/0/all/0/1">here on the arxiv!</a> You can find my Ph.D. manuscript, in French, <a href="http://arxiv.org/abs/1009.5100">here</a>.
</dd>
<br>
<br>
<dd>I have had 20 co-authors, including 7 Master or Ph.D. students.
</dd>
<dd><em>More stats</em> from the high energy physics database <a href="http://inspirehep.net/author/profile/V.Bonzom.1">here</a>!
</dd>
</div>
