<br>
<dd>Recent preprints: the stuff I am excited about in these days!
<ul>
<li>"Duality between Spin networks and the 2D Ising model,'' VB, Francesco Costantino and Etera R. Livine. <a href="http://arxiv.org/abs/1504.02822">arxiv:1504.02822</a>
</li>
<li>"Enhancing non-melonic triangulations: A tensor model mixing melonic and planar maps,'' VB, Thibault Delepouve and Vincent Rivasseau. Accepted in <em>Nucl. Phys. B</em>. <a href="http://arxiv.org/abs/1502.01365">arxiv:1502.01365</a>
</li>
<li>"Deformed phase space for 3d loop gravity and hyperbolic discrete geometries," VB, Mait&eacute Dupuis, Florian Girelli, Etera R. Livine. <a href="http://arxiv.org/abs/1402.2323">arXiv:1402.2323</a>
</li>
</ul>
</dd>

<br>
<dd>More accessible, introductory/survey articles
<ul>
<li>"Tensor models from the viewpoint of matrix models: the case of loop models on random surfaces," VB and Fr&eacuted&eacuteric Combes. <em>Annales Henri Poincar&eacute D</em> 2, 1 (2015). <a href="http://arxiv.org/abs/1304.4152">arXiv:1304.4152</a>
</li>
<li>"Random tensor models in the large N limit: Uncoloring the colored tensor models," VB, Razvan Gurau and Vincent Rivasseau. <em>Phys. Rev. D</em> 85, 084037 (2012). <a href="http://arxiv.org/abs/1202.3637">arXiv:1202.3637</a>
</li>
<li>"Gauge symmetries in spinfoam gravity: the case for "cellular quantization"," VB and Matteo Smerlak. <em>Phys. Rev. Lett.</em> 108, 241303 (2012). <a href="http://arxiv.org/abs/1201.4996">arXiv:1201.4996</a>
</li>
<li>"Lessons from Toy-Models for the Dynamics of Loop Quantum Gravity," VB and Alok Laddha. <em>SIGMA</em> 8 (2012), 009. <a href="http://arxiv.org/abs/1110.2157">arXiv:1110.2157</a>
</li>
<li>"Bubble divergences: sorting out topology from cell structure," VB and Matteo Smerlak. <em>Annales Henri Poincar&eacute</em> 13 (2012) 185. <a href="http://arxiv.org/abs/1103.3961">arXiv:1103.3961</a>
</ul>
</dd>

<br>
<dd>Selected publications
<ul>
<li>"The calculation of expectation values in Gaussian random tensor theory via meanders," VB and Fr&eacuted&eacuteric Combes, <em>Annales Henri Poincar&eacute D</em> 1, 443<!--485--> (2015). <a href="http://arxiv.org/abs/1310.3606">arXiv:1310.3606</a>
</li>
<li>"Critical behavior of colored tensor models in the large N limit," VB, Razvan Gurau, Aldo Riello and Vincent Rivasseau, <em>Nucl. Phys. B</em> 853, 174 (2011). <a href="http://arxiv.org/abs/1105.3122">arXiv:1105.3122</a>
</li>
<li>"Dirac's discrete hypersurface deformation algebras," VB and Bianca Dittrich, <em>Class. Quant. Grav.</em> 30 (2013) 205013. <a href="http://arxiv.org/abs/1304.5983">arXiv:1304.5983</a> 
<li>"Bubble divergences from twisted cohomology," VB and Matteo Smerlak, <em> Commun. Math. Phys.</em> 312, 399 (2012). <a href="http://arxiv.org/abs/1008.1476">arXiv:1008.1476</a>
</li>
</ul>

<br>
<dt><div class="box"></div><b>CV</b></dt>
<br>
<dd>I am an Assistant Professor at IUT Saint-Denis, France, and a member of the Laboratoire d'Informatique de Paris Nord (<a href="https://lipn.univ-paris13.fr/en/">LIPN</a>) in the team <em>Combinatoire, ALgorithmique et INteractions</em> (<a href="https://lipn.univ-paris13.fr/en/calin">CALIN</a>). I was offered that position in 2013. 
</dd>
<br>
<dd>Before that, I was a postdoctoral fellow at Perimeter Institute for Theoretical Physics, Waterloo, Ontario, Canada, from 2010 to 2013. I was supported by a MRI grant from the Government of Ontario. In 2013 I was a recipient of the Banting Fellowship, which I declined in favor of my present position.
</dd>
</dl>

